<p><strong>Once upon a time in New York City</strong>, we started a software consultancy based on the fact that there are a ton of up and coming startups here in Silicon Alley. It worked, but not nearly as well as we hoped. Here's ultimately what we learned from our experience:</p>
<ol>
<li>Startups work on some very cool stuff</li>
<li>Startups have no money</li>
</ol>
<p>Obvious huh? Yeah well, our thought was that there were so many of them that they would keep us in business for a while. Oh and that they did! However, we had two problems:</p>
<ul>
<li>We were too busy (not a problem by itself, but…)</li>
<li>We weren't making enough money</li>
</ul>
